Hand Gesture Modeling, Analysis and Synthesis
3 motion phases : preparation, stroke (increased speed) and retractation(returning to rest position)
mvt des doigts a du sens seulement si la main est fixe
modèle :
static hand gestures : hand posture -> finger-thumb-palm configuration
dynamic hand gestures : general stroke motion + begin/end hand configuration
-> pdt mvt, chgt de configuration n'apporte pas d'information

gesture analysis : temporal and spatial
Glove-Talk : 203 gesture-to-words
vision-based analysis : palm-orientation/joint angles
feature tracking and model parameter estimation -> Gauss-Newton min of the residual feature error
Lee and Kuni -> model 27 degrees of freedom
Kuch 300 point Nurbs-based handmodel -> 26degrees of freedom
Davis and Shah  computed motion trajectories (marqueurs) -> start/end of gesture
-> gesture modeled by a set of start-end vectors
-> cylindrical fingertip model
Maggiono -> image geometry parameters based on 1stnand 2d moments -> estimation hand position and orientation
..


